main event: Several unidentified objects were observed by personnel on a ship and in the air in the Hawaiian Islands in 1966.
interesting points: The objects appeared to originate with a bright flash, leaving behind a short vapor trail.
On one occasion, the objects appeared to number 5-6 to 12, all appearing as red streaks and trailing fire.
The objects traveled at varying speeds, some too fast for an aircraft and too slow for a meteor.
The objects were observed by both civilian and military personnel, who were considered highly reliable observers.
A rocket body for an Agena adapter vehicle was confirmed to have come down in the area at the time of the sightings.
sighted object: Several unidentified objects, some appearing as red streaks and others as a single light with a short vapor trail
witnesses: Civilian and military personnel on a ship and in the air
